marshall fields is the homegrown favorite in 
this citys retail game now an invader from new york will sell its 
wares on michigan avenue raising a question for people with power 
in their pocketbooks 
gosh dahling whats a shopper to do 
bloomingdales big apple boss gotham giant 59th street 
strongman is opening saturday a sixfloor home a few blocks from 
lake michigan and there is gleeful speculation around town about 
which retailer will have the registers ringing 
for a while there will be blood in the streets says bill 
zwecker a society columnist who monitors the pulse of chicagos 
upper crust for the skyline weekly newspaper 
most people recognize this is a bloomingdalesfields 
battle he said its been building up to a crescendo there 
has been an electricity to this arrival that i have never seen 
and when it comes to keeping customers happy a little partying 
cant hurt 
