general manager brian mcmahon says bloomingdales will be 
staffed by people who will earn only commissions on sales no 
salary a first for the 17store chain and a policy believed to 
improve customer service 
you name the store in the city of chicago weve ben able to 
get the best people and bring them in he said of recruiting a 
sales team its only going to be a coup if we exercise the 
service well 
this market has created more interest in a store opening than 
any ive ever been connected with and ive lived in washington 
new york and boston mcmahon said 
its certainly uplifting but ive tried to tell everybody to 
retain a high level of humility theres nothing worse than 
building up a crescendo believing your own press and then having a 
shopper come in and say this isnt what i expected 
at marshall fields reaction to bloomingdales opening is 
lowkey 
our game plan is to compete effectively against all 
competitors and bloomingdales is one them said gary witkin 
executive vice president 
i think our attitude about business is no different today than 
it was a year ago 
