<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on 
lebanon 
the land lebanon lies in the eastern mediterranean and covers 
4034 square miles from a narrow coastal strip the land rises 
steeply into the mt lebanon range with the highest peak at qurnet 
alsawdah 9000 feet 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people moslems make up around 55 percent of the estimated 
3 million population and christians once considerd the majority 
make up about 45 percent lebanon has 17 religious sects with the 
biggest the millionstrong shiite moslems the countrys makeup 
which has contributed to much of lebanons sectarian bloodshed 
reflects the waves of people who fled persecution and took refuge 
in the rugged mountains through the centuries about 500000 
palestinian refugees live in lebanon 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy lebanon has no natural resources so the people 
have since ancient times turned to commerce the most prominent 
were the phoenicians before the civil war began in 1975 lebanon 
was the financial center of the middle east with one of the 
strongest currencies it was also a major tourist center the war 
has gutted the economy 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history some lebanese claim descent from the phoenicians who 
lived in the area 6000 years ago the assyrians persians romans 
byzantines crusaders mamalukes and arabs all have ruled what is 
now lebanon until it fell under the ottoman empire in the 16th 
century ottoman rule ended with world war i lebanon was put under 
a french mandate until independence in 1943 the christians 
dominated but moslem demands for political reforms helped trigger 
the civil war in 1975 an estimated 150000 people have been killed 
in the fighting and intervention by the syrians israelis and the 
united states the war has dismembered lebanon into sectarian 
cantons as well as sectors controlled by syria and israel leaving 
lebanon a country in name only 
</TEXT>
