the days of the big slab of beef are over 
replaced by exotic ethnic recipes featuring bitesize pieces more 
palatable to healthconscious americans according to cooks at the 
national beef cookoff 
sixtytwo of the best beef cooks in the nation brought their 
favorite pans woks and ladles to the deep south this week in 
search of the title of best beef cook in the nation and the 15000 
grand prize 
and most were betting on recipes with an international flavor 
and smaller pieces of meat 
theres still quite a strong sustained mexican influence 
oriental is also coming through but not just the typical stir 
