<TEXT>
a jury that convicted a former mexican 
policeman in the 1985 kidnap and torture murder of a us drug 
enforcement administration agent returned to deliberate on the 
guilt or innocence of two codefendants 
the panel convicted raul lopez alvarez on thursday lopez was 
videotaped telling an undercover officer about events surrounding 
the brutal murder of dea agent enrique camarena whose battered 
body was found along with that of his pilot at a ranch outside 
guadalajara on march 5 1985 
on the videotape the former mexican lawman described the 
slaying of camarena as a mistake by drug baron rafael caro 
quintero adding the idea wasnt to kill him 
after a single days deliberation the jury found lopez 28 
guilty of kidnap murder conspiracy and related crimes in the 
killing of camarena and pilot alfredo zavala avelar 
jurors announced their first verdict thursday morning then 
resumed deliberating for a full day 
they recessed without deciding the cases of two codefendants 
rene verdugo urquidez 36 a confessed drug trafficker and jesus 
felix guttierez who is charged as an accessory after the fact 
the government alleges that guttierez helped the drug baron 
escape from mexico after caro allegedly masterminded camarenas 
murder as revenge for dea raids on the drug barons multimillion 
dollar marijuana operations in mexico 
lopez who grew up in the los angeles area but returned to his 
native mexico was a member of the state judicial police assigned 
to the homicide squad in guadalajara in 1985 
the role of mexican police in the drugrelated murders made the 
case politically sensitive and engendered bitter feelings between 
mexican and american investigators 
lopez was found guilty of six charges including two counts of 
committing violent acts in support of racketeering 
prosecutors said this conviction was the first in the nation 
under that new section of racketeering law aimed at drugrelated 
crimes 
lopez also was found guilty of conspiracy to kidnap kidnapping 
felony murder and accessory after the fact 
lopez lawyer yolanda barrera told jurors in final arguments 
that lopez fabricated the story heard on the videotape from 
accounts he read in newspapers to inflate his own importance to the 
agent he believed was a drug dealer 
she said the only evidence against him was his mouth and 
urged jurors not to believe his statements 
mr lopez alvarez ended up in this trial for acting like a 
child she said he is a man caught up in the web of his own 
lies he told one lie too many 
us district judge edward rafeedie set lopezs sentencing for 
oct 24 he faces a maximum sentence of life in prison 
camarena was abducted feb 7 1985 in guadalajara as he left 
the us consulate to meet his wife for lunch 
the bodies of camarena and his pilot were found buried at a 
remote ranch they were severely beaten and camarenas skull was 
crushed 
nine men were indicted in los angeles in the camarena slaying 
but only three are standing trial here caro 33 and three other 
defendants are in custody and awaiting trial on related charges in 
mexico an eighth man has died and another is a fugitive 
