examination that the nozzle inlet ring installed in the aug 18 
test booster contained the old design morton thiokol said the old 
ring performed satisfactorily 
the rings are inside the nozzle assembly at the tail of the 
126footlong shuttle booster they are not the orings in the 
booster segment joints that were blamed for the jan 28 1986 
explosion of the shuttle challenger 
the nozzle inlet ring has been only slightly modified since 
then while the segment joints have been extensively redesigned 
