<TEXT>
sheldon coleman chairman of the coleman 
co who spearheaded its diversification from camp stoves and 
lanterns to air conditioning equipment and outdoors gear has died 
he was 86 
coleman son of the companys founder died wednesday night of 
pneumonia at a hospital his family said 
we will miss him immeasurably said his son sheldon c 
coleman company president and chief operating officer 
the elder coleman joined his fathers company in 1925 shortly 
after graduating from cornell university with a mechanical 
engineering degree he became coleman co chief executive officer 
and executive vice president in october 1940 and was elected 
chairman of the board in 1957 
the company was founded by wc coleman in 1900 in kingfisher 
okla as a lightingservice business leasing lamps and servicing 
them in 1901 the business moved to wichita where it began 
producing lamps in 1905 it developed its famous coleman lanterns 
which lengthened the farmers day in 1914 
in 1920s lamp and lantern production boomed but the coleman 
family almost lost the company during the great depression 
coleman saw rural electrification coming and recommended the 
company diversify by developing oil space heaters and gas floor 
furnaces in the 1930s it still produces heating and air 
conditioning equipment including units for mobile homes and 
recreational vehicles 
during the 1960s coleman led another diversification expanding 
lantern and camp stove production into dozens of outdoor recreation 
products the company eventually became the worlds largest 
manufacturer of such items 
last year the publicly held company which has more than 5000 
employees had record sales of nearly 600 million 
coleman was active in a number of civic and professional 
organizations serving as vice chairman of the board of governors 
of the american red cross a member of the national council of the 
boy scouts of america and on president reagans commission on 
americans outdoors 
besides his son coleman is survived by his wife galey a 
brother clarence two daughters two stepsons a stepdaughter 14 
grandchildren and five greatgrandchildren 
the funeral is scheduled saturday at metropolitan baptist church 
in wichita 
</TEXT>
